# NestJS Exception Handling Rules
- All controllers, services, and guards must handle exceptions using NestJS built-in exception classes.
- When an exception occurs, return a clear HTTP status code and message.
- For custom exceptions, extend the NestJS Exception class.
- Exception messages must be written in Korean.
- Exception handling logic must be documented with sufficient Korean comments.
- Log exceptions, but do not include sensitive information in logs.
- Follow the official NestJS exception handling documentation patterns.
